                englishText: "Some people from the Anṣār (Helpers) asked the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) for something so he gave them. They again asked him and he again gave them. This continued until whatever he had was depleted. When he had given everything, he said to them: \"I will never withhold from you what I possess. However, Allāh (ﷻ) gives chastity to the one who seeks it, Allāh (ﷻ) gives independence to the one who seeks it and Allāh (ﷻ) gives patience to the one who exercises patience. No person has been given a gift that is better and greater than that of patience.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
