                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) was asked: \"Who is the noblest of people?\" He replied: \"The person who fears Allāh the most.\" The Ṣaḥābah said: \"That is not what we meant.\" He said: \"Yūsuf, a Messenger of Allāh, a son of a Messenger of Allāh, a son of a Messenger of Allāh, a son of a bosom friend of Allāh (Ibrāhīm عليه السلام).\" The Ṣaḥābah said: \"That is not what we meant.\" He said: \"Are you then asking me about the Arab tribes? Those who were the best of them in Jāhiliyyah (pre-Islāmic era of ignorance) are the best of them in Islām provided they have knowledge (of Islām).\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
