                englishText: "Three people came to the houses of the Messenger of Allāh's (ﷺ) wives, inquiring about the worship of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ). When they were informed, it was as if they considered it little. They then said among themselves: 'We can never compare with the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) as all his past and future sins are forgiven.' One of them said: 'I will remain awake every night in order to perform the Tahajjud ṣalāh.' The second person said: 'I will fast everyday without ifṭār.' The third person said: 'I will withdraw from women and never marry.' The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) then came to them and asked: 'Are you the ones who made such and such statements? By Allāh, I fear Allāh more than you do and I am more conscious of Him than you are, yet, I fast and I break the fast, I offer ṣalāh and I sleep, and I marry. Whoever is disinclined to my Sunnah is not of me.'\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
