                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `Fire has been referred to as an \"enemy\" despite its benefits because of its general potential of causing damage to life and wealth. The command in this ḥadīth has to do with safety and well-being in daily life. Caution in such matters ensures the protection of life and wealth. It is common, even today to hear of fires starting from electrical heating appliances left switched on negligently. The ḥadīth illustrates the mercy of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) upon the Ummah as he showed concern for our worldly safety as well as our spiritual well-being. Any form of light or heat that is controlled or harmless may be left on when one goes to sleep.`
