                commentary: `One should be cautious not to initiate evil because one who does so will be equal in the sin of others who perpetuate it. Qābīl's sister who was to be married to Hābīl was more beautiful than Hābīl's sister who was to be married to Qābīl. Qābīl therefore wanted to marry his own sister, but as this was not permissible, he murdered his brother out of jealousy. Due to his evil action, he will continue to earn the sin of every murder because he was the first to initiate it. Shaiṭān drives a person towards jealousy, which in turn leads towards other forms of sin such as murder.`
