                englishText: "I pledged allegiance to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) for establishing ṣalāh, paying zakāh and giving advice to every Muslim.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `The importance of advising others can be gauged from the fact that it has been mentioned in the same breath as ṣalāh and zakāh. Furthermore, the ḥadīth states that the Ṣaḥābah would take a pledge regarding it just as they pledged to fulfil other injunctions of Islām. Jarīr ibn 'Abdullāh (رضي الله عنه), the narrator of the ḥadīth, practically implemented this injunction by paying eight hundred dirhams for a horse, which its owner had priced at three hundred because he felt that it was worth more.`
