                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"When a slave woman commits fornication and it is proven, she should be flogged and not rebuked. If she then commits fornication a second time, she should again be flogged and not rebuked. If she then commits fornication a third time, he (i.e. the master) should sell her even if it be for a rope made of fibres.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
