                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Do not beat the female servants of Allāh.\" 'Umar (رضي الله عنه) then came to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) and said: \"The women have become bold before their husbands.\" So, the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) gave a concession to strike women. Many women began to come to the family of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) complaining about their husbands. So the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Many women have come to the family of Muḥammad, complaining about their husbands. Such men are not the best of you.\" (Abū Dāwūd)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Abu Dawud",
                commentary: `The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) gave the concession to beat rebellious women lightly because this is better than divorce or a life of misery in this world. The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) created a balance, allowing a husband to beat his wife lightly, but also stating that one who does so is not the best of men in character.`
