                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"When a husband calls his wife to bed and she does not come to him and he spends the night angry with her, the angels curse her until the morning.\" Another narration of Bukhārī and Muslim has: \"When a woman spends the night forsaking her husband's bed, the angels curse her until the morning.\" In another narration the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"I take an oath in the name of that Being in whose control is my life, when a man calls his wife to his bed and she refuses him, the Being who is in the heavens is angry with her until her husband becomes pleased with her.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
