                commentary: `This ḥadīth emphasises the importance of the wife honouring and obeying her husband. Abū Dāwūd narrates the background for this ḥadīth. Qais ibn Sa'd stated that he went to Ḥīrā and noticed its inhabitants prostrating to their leader. He thought to himself, \"The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) is more worthy of being prostrated to.\" He then came to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) and informed him about what he saw. The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said, \"If you pass by my grave, will you prostrate to me?\" He replied, \"No.\" The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) then said, \"Then do not do so. If I were to command anyone to prostrate to anyone else, I would have commanded the woman to prostrate before her husband.\"`
