                englishText: "From among the Anṣār, Abū Ṭalḥah (رضي الله عنه) owned the most date orchards in Madīnah and from all his wealth, his orchard, Bayraḥā', which was in front of the Masjid (al-Nabawī) was dearest to him. The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) used to enter it and drink its sweet water.\" Anas (رضي الله عنه) continues: \"When this verse was revealed: 'You will never be able to acquire perfection in virtue until you spend something of that which you love', Abū Ṭalḥah (رضي الله عنه) went to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) and said: 'O Messenger of Allāh! Allāh revealed this verse to you: 'You will never be able to acquire perfection in virtue until you spend something of that which you love.' The most beloved of all my wealth is Bayraḥā'. I give it in charity for the sake of Allāh and I am hopeful for its goodness and reward from Allāh. So, O Messenger of Allāh, you may distribute this orchard as Allāh directs you.' The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: 'Excellent. That is very profitable wealth. That is very profitable wealth. I have heard what you said and I feel that you should distribute it among your close relatives.' Abū Ṭalḥah (رضي الله عنه) said: 'I will do so, O Messenger of Allāh!' He (رضي الله عنه) then distributed it among his close relatives and cousins.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
