                arabicText: "وعن أبي الدرداء رضي الله عنه : أن رجلاً آتاه ، قَالَ : إنَّ لِي امرأةً وإنَّ أُمِّي تأمُرُني بِطَلاقِهَا ؟ فَقَالَ : سَمِعْتُ رَسُولَ الله صلى الله عليه وسلم ، يقول : (( الوَالِدُ أَوْسَطُ أَبْوَابِ الجَنَّةِ ، فَإنْ شِئْتَ ، فَأَضِعْ ذلِكَ البَابَ ، أَوْ احْفَظْهُ )) رواه الترمذي ، وَقالَ : (( حديث حسن صحيح )) .",
                englishText: "A man came to him and said: \"I have a wife and my mother is ordering me to divorce her.\" He said: \"I heard the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) saying: 'The parent is the middle gate of Paradise. You may either destroy that door or safeguard it.'\" (Tirmidhī)",
                grade: "Hasan Sahih",
                collection: "Tirmidhi",
                commentary: `The man approached Abū al-Dardā' (رضي الله عنه) because he was uncertain about divorcing his wife, due to his love for her. Abū al-Dardā' (رضي الله عنه) advised that he should obey his parents. As explained in the previous ḥadīth, it is necessary to obey one's parents in matters that conform to sharī'ah. The parent is described as the middle gate of Paradise, which is the best gate. This means that being obedient to parents is one of the best means of entering Paradise.`
