                commentary: `Anas (رضي الله عنه) objected to Jarīr ibn 'Abdullāh (رضي الله عنه) serving him because the latter was older than he was. From this, we learn three lessons. Firstly, it points to the virtue and humility of Jarīr ibn 'Abdullāh (رضي الله عنه), his kindness to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) and to those who served the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ). Secondly, it teaches us to honour and serve the righteous and those associated with them, even though they may be younger. Thirdly, the fact that the Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم) served the servants of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) illustrates their degree of love for him.`
