                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"If three qualities are found in a person, he will experience the sweetness of īmān: that Allāh (ﷻ) and His Messenger (ﷺ) are more beloved to him than everything else; that he loves a person only for the sake of Allāh (ﷻ); and that he detests returning to unbelief after Allāh (ﷻ) rescued him from it, just as he detests being cast into a fire.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `This ḥadīth is among the fundamentals of Islām. Love for Allāh (ﷻ) and His Messenger (ﷺ) is achieved by acting in obedience to Allāh's (ﷻ) commands. According to the Mufassir Qāḍī Bayḍāwī, this refers to intellectual love, which means to give preference to that which an intellectually healthy mind would prefer, even if it is against one's desires. The ḥadīth states that it is better to be thrown into a worldly fire than to perpetrate kufr, because kufr will result in punishment in the fire of the Hereafter, which is many times more intense.`
