                commentary: `The Anṣār supported the Muhājirīn with everything they had, showing more generosity to them than even blood brothers. The Qur'ān speaks highly of them for their great sacrifice to the cause of Islām, and the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) too advised his Ummah to love them and hold them in their rightful esteem. A believer can only be filled with love and admiration for these giants of Islām. Love for them is a testimony of the truth of one's faith because it proves that one is content with those whom Allāh (ﷻ) and His Messenger (ﷺ) were pleased. Anyone who, in spite of all this, harbours any ill feeling towards them is not a believer but a hypocrite. Loving them attracts the love of Allāh (ﷻ) and one who hates them brings upon himself the anger and hatred of Allāh (ﷻ).`
