                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) held him by his hand and said: \"O Mu'ādh! By Allāh, I love you. O Mu'ādh! I advise you never to neglect saying these words after every (obligatory) ṣalāh: 'Allāhumma a'innī 'alā dhikrika, wa shukrika, wa ḥusni 'ibādatik' (O Allāh! Help me to engage in Your remembrance, in showing gratitude to You and in worshipping You in an excellent way).\" (Abū Dāwūd, Nasā'ī)",
                grade: "Sahih",
