                commentary: `The Messenger of Allāh's (ﷺ) action of holding Mu'ādh's (رضي الله عنه) hand and telling him that he loved him had the effect of emphasising the lesson he was about to impart to him. A student who perceives a sense of affection from his teacher is more likely to accept his teachings. This also shows the extraordinary virtue of Mu'ādh (رضي الله عنه) and his closeness to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ). The du'ā' taught by the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) teaches us that fulfilling our duty to Allāh (ﷻ) can only be done with the help of Allāh (ﷻ) Himself. We should therefore express our weakness and inability before Allāh (ﷻ) in order to attract His mercy and assistance.`
