                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) addressed us in a sermon the like of which I have never heard. He said: 'If you only knew what I know, you would laugh little and cry much.' On hearing this, the Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم) covered their faces and began weeping.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim). Another narration has: \"The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) heard something about his Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم). He therefore addressed them saying: 'Paradise and the Hell-fire were presented before me and I have not seen a day like this day in respect of good and evil. If you only knew what I know, you will laugh little and cry much.' Never did the Ṣaḥābah experience a more severe day than this. They covered their heads and began weeping.\"",
