                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"How can I enjoy life when the angel who has been deputed to blow the trumpet has already placed it in his mouth, with his ear turned in order to listen to the order to blow it so that he may blow it?\" This statement weighed heavily on the Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم) of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ), so he said to them: \"Say: 'Allāh is sufficient for us and an excellent guardian is He.'\" (Tirmidhī)",
