                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"One who fears departs in the first portion of the night and one who departs in the first portion of the night reaches his destination. Know that the commodity of Allāh is expensive. Know that the commodity of Allāh is Paradise.\" (Tirmidhī)",
                grade: "Hasan",
                collection: "Tirmidhi",
                commentary: `In this ḥadīth, a real life situation has been used to explain the importance of hastening towards good deeds. A traveller may be attacked by an enemy in the darkest hours of the night. One who fears such an attack will begin travelling early in the night, so that he can safely reach his destination. Similarly, our destination is the Hereafter, where we hope to live blissfully in Paradise. We must be courageous and hasten to perform good actions.`
