                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Allāh (ﷻ) said: 'I treat My servant according to his expectations of Me. I am with him wherever he remembers Me.' By Allāh, Allāh (ﷻ) is more pleased with the repentance of His servant then one of you who finds his lost conveyance and possessions in a barren land. 'Whoever comes close to Me by one span, I go closer to him by one hand span. One who approaches Me by a hand span, I approach him by an arm-span. If he comes to Me walking, I go to him running.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `This ḥadīth encourages us to have hope in the mercy of Allāh (ﷻ) and to hasten towards repentance. According to Imām Qurṭubī (رحمه الله), \"I treat My servant according to his expectations of Me\" applies to du'ā', tawbah and istighfār. In other words, Allāh (ﷻ) will accept du'ā' and repentance if a person has the faith that Allāh (ﷻ) has accepted it. The ḥadīth also tells of Allāh's (ﷻ) great pleasure at his servant's turning to Him in repentance.`
