                narrator: "Abdullāh ibn Mas'ūd (رضي الله عنه)",
                arabicText: "وعن عبد الله بن مسعود رضي الله عنه ، قَالَ : قَالَ رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : (( لاَ تَتَّخِذُوا الضَّيْعَةَ فَتَرْغَبُوا فِي الدُّنْيَا )) رواه الترمذي ، وقال : (( حديثٌ حسنٌ )) .",
                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Do not hanker after property so much that you become engrossed in this world.\" (Tirmidhī)",
                grade: "Hasan",
                collection: "Tirmidhi",
                commentary: `Property acquisition and development are despised when these become the focus and objective of life and lead one away from Allāh's worship. However, one who engages in them for the benefit of humanity, while adhering to Allāh's laws, is not included in the ambit of this ḥadīth. While property development has been singled out, scholars have extended it to include any occupation, skill or employment which man engages in.`
