                englishText: "I came to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) while he was reciting Sūrah al-Takāthur - \"The mutual rivalry for increasing worldly things diverts you.\" He said: \"Man says: 'My wealth, my wealth.' O man! Do you possess any other wealth except what you ate and digested, or wore and wore out, or gave in charity and sent it forward (for the Hereafter)?'\" (Muslim)",
