                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"The most truthful statement ever said by a poet was that of Labīd: 'Listen! Everything apart from Allāh (ﷻ) is baseless.'\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `The full verse of Labīd's poem was: \"Everything apart from Allāh is baseless; and every bounty will definitely be depleted.\" This means that everything except Allāh will perish. This conforms to the Qur'ānic verse: \"Everything on earth shall perish.\" (Sūrah al-Raḥmān, 26) The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) never composed any poetry, however he sometimes quoted the beneficial poetry of others. From this, we learn that poetry is in itself not despised. It is encouraged if it is beneficial, otherwise not.`
