                englishText: "A man came to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) and said: \"I am suffering (due to hunger).\" So the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) sent someone to one of his wives, but she replied: \"By the One who sent you with the truth, I have nothing but water.\" Then he sent to another wife, who said the same thing, until all of them had said: \"By the One who sent you with the truth, I have nothing but water.\" The Prophet (ﷺ) then said: \"Who will host this person tonight?\" A man from the Anṣār said: \"I, O Messenger of Allāh.\" He then took him to his home and said to his wife: \"Honour the guest of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ).\" In another narration, he said to his wife: \"Do you have anything?\" She replied: \"No, only my children's food.\" He said: \"Distract them with something and when they want their supper, put them to sleep. When our guest enters, extinguish the lamp and show him that we are eating.\" So they sat down and the guest ate, while they spent the night hungry. When morning came, he went to the Prophet (ﷺ), who said: \"Allāh was amazed by what you and your wife did for your guest tonight.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
