                arabicText: "وعن النَّوَّاسِ بن سمعان رضي الله عنه ، قَالَ : سَألتُ رسُولَ الله صلى الله عليه وسلم عن البِرِّ والإِثْمِ ، فقَالَ : (( البِرُّ : حُسْنُ الخُلُقِ ، والإِثْمُ : مَا حَاكَ فِي صَدْرِكَ ، وكَرِهْتَ أَنْ يَطَّلِعَ عَلَيْهِ النَّاسُ )) رواه مسلم .",
                englishText: "I asked the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) about righteousness and sin. He said: 'Righteousness is good character, and sin is that which creates doubt within you and you dislike that people become aware of it.'\" (Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Muslim",
                commentary: `This ḥadīth was mentioned in a previous chapter. See ḥadīth 590. It is relevant to this chapter because it teaches us that the best form of righteousness is to be embodied with admirable character.`
