                commentary: `Scholars state that the mention of a believer in this ḥadīth indicates that the actions of a disbeliever will have no weight on the day of Qiyāmah because he lacks the qualifying attribute of īmān. In other words, good character will only benefit a person when it is coupled with īmān. The Qur'ān confirms this: \"And no weight will be attached to them on the day of Qiyāmah.\" (Sūrah al-Kahf, 105)`
