                englishText: "He said to Mu'āwiyah (رضي الله عنه): \"I heard the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) saying: 'When Allāh (ﷻ) appoints a person over the affairs of the Muslims and he is blind to their needs, necessities and poverty, Allāh (ﷻ) will be blind to his needs, necessities and poverty on the day of Qiyāmah.'\" Mu'āwiyah (رضي الله عنه) therefore appointed a person to see to the needs of the people. (Abū Dāwūd, Tirmidhī)",
