                englishText: "I visited the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) with two of my cousins. One of them said: 'O Messenger of Allāh! Appoint us as governors over places which Allāh (ﷻ) has granted you authority.' The other cousin also made a similar request. He (ﷺ) said: 'By Allāh, we will not appoint any person to such a post if he asks for it or desires it.'\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
