                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) was eating food with six of his Ṣaḥābah, when a Bedouin came along and ate it all up in two morsels. The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: 'If he had taken the name of Allāh (ﷻ), it would have been enough for all of you.'\" (Tirmidhī)",
