                englishText: "We were afflicted by a year of drought during the khilāfah of ('Abdullāh) ibn Zubayr (رضي الله عنه) and we were given some dates. 'Abdullāh ibn 'Umar (رضي الله عنهما) passed by us while we were eating and said: 'Do not eat two at the same time because the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) forbade eating two at the same time.' He then said: 'Unless a person asks his companion for permission.'\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
