                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) had a bowl which was called al-Gharrā' and it was carried by four people. When it was mid-morning and the Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم) had offered the ṣalāt al-Ḍuḥā, the bowl would be brought, filled with tharīd and they would sit around it. When they became many, the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) sat on his knees. A Bedouin asked: 'What is this way of sitting?' The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) replied: 'Surely Allāh has made me a noble servant, and He did not make me an arrogant person.' Then the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: 'Eat from its sides, and leave its top so that blessings may be placed in it.'\" (Abū Dāwūd)",
