                collection: "Muslim",
                commentary: `The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) mostly wore a white turban, however he wore a black turban when in jihād because black conceals signs of dust, etc. Also it served as an indication that Islām would not change just as black does not change, in contrast to other colours. Islām has not restricted the wearing of a turban to that of any single colour, however if a certain colour becomes the distinguishing factor of a particular misguided group or religion in an area, then one should abstain from wearing that colour so that one does not resemble them.`
