                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `Saḥūlī cotton is attributed to the place of its origin, which is a place in Yemen. 'Allāmah 'Ainī (رحمه الله) stated that during the era of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ), garments from Yemen were popular among the Arabs. They were made from cotton and had red or green stripes. It is preferable for men to be enshrouded in three garments, and it is best that they are white, as the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) commanded. See ḥadīth 779, 780.`
