                narrator: "Amr ibn Shu'ayb narrates from his father from his grandfather that the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ)",
                arabicText: "عن عمرو بن شعيب ، عن أبيه ، عن جَدِّهِ رضي الله عنه ، قَالَ: قَالَ رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : (( إِنَّ اللَّهَ يُحِبُّ أَنْ يَرَى أَثَرَ نِعْمَتِهِ عَلَى عَبْدِهِ )) رواه الترمذي ، وقال : (( حديث حسن )) .",
                englishText: "Allāh (ﷻ) loves to see the effects of His bounties on His servant.\" (Tirmidhī)",
                grade: "Hasan",
                collection: "Tirmidhi",
                commentary: `When Allāh bestows a worldly bounty on a person, he should utilise it, but ensure that he does not indulge in wastage and extravagance. One should not utilise it with pride and show, but with the intention of being grateful for the bounty granted by Allāh. A boastful garment refers to any such garment which a person wears so that he may be the centre of attention. The best is for a person to wear average clothing - neither that which draws attention due to its excellence, nor that which draws attention due to its reprehensible nature.`
