                commentary: `This prohibition refers to animal skins which have not been tanned; since they are impure, it is not permissible to sit on them. Generally, even the tanning process does not render such animal skins pure because impure hair remains attached to the skin, hence the prohibition. Some scholars state that the prohibition is because the proud and affluent utilise the skins of animals of prey, hence we are advised to avoid resemblance with them.`
