                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"A person who performs ghusl on the day of Jumu'ah, purifies himself to the best of his ability, applies oil or puts on any perfume he has in his house, then goes out and does not separate between two people, performs whatever ṣalāh is prescribed for him, and is silent when the Imām speaks, then he is forgiven for sins committed from then until the next Jumu'ah.\" (Bukhārī)",
