                commentary: `This ḥadīth encourages the recitation of this du'ā' at the end of gatherings. Even the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) would recite this du'ā', seeking forgiveness for any shortcomings in the gathering. It also shows that the Ṣaḥābah would observe the actions of the Messenger (ﷺ) very closely and would enquire about any new practices they observed.`
