                collection: "Abu Dawud",
                commentary: `The Messenger (ﷺ) affirmed good actions and qualities that were prevalent before the advent of his prophethood, and he rejected evils. The practice of shaking hands was common amongst the people of Yemen and the Messenger (ﷺ) approved of it when they came to meet him, hence, it is regarded as Sunnah.`
