                englishText: "We attended a funeral in Baqī' al-Gharqad. The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) came to us and sat down, so we sat down around him. He was holding a stick and he lowered his head and began prodding the ground with the stick. He then said: \"Every one of you has his place in the Hell-fire and in Paradise written for him.\" The Ṣaḥābah asked: \"O Messenger of Allāh, should we not then rely on what has been written for us?\" He replied: \"Perform good deeds because every person is inspired to do the deeds for which he was created.\" He then related the entire ḥadīth. (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
