                englishText: "Abū al-Aswad narrates: \"I came to Madīnah and sat in the company of 'Umar ibn al-Khaṭṭāb (رضي الله عنه). A funeral passed by and people praised the deceased. 'Umar (رضي الله عنه) said: 'It is compulsory.' Then another funeral passed by and people praised the deceased. 'Umar (رضي الله عنه) said: 'It is compulsory.' Then a third funeral passed by and people spoke evil of the deceased. 'Umar (رضي الله عنه) said: 'It is compulsory.' I asked: 'What is compulsory, O Amīr al-Mu'minīn?' He replied: 'I said as the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: 'When four people testify to the goodness of a deceased Muslim, Allāh admits him into Paradise.' We asked: 'What about three?' He said: 'Even three.' We asked: 'What about two?' He said: 'Even two.' We did not ask him about one.'\" (Bukhārī)",
