                arabicText: "وعن أَبي مالك الأشعري رضي الله عنه ، قَالَ : قَالَ رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : (( الطُّهُورُ شَطْرُ الإِيمَانِ )) رواه مسلم . وَقَدْ سبق بطوله في باب الصبر .",
                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Purity is half of faith.\" (Muslim, Aḥmad, Bayhaqī)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Muslim",
                commentary: `The ḥadīth has been repeated here to show the virtue of purity and wuḍū'. \"Purity is half of faith,\" may have one of several meanings: Īmān (faith) refers to ṣalāh, hence the ḥadīth means that wuḍū' is an integral part of ṣalāh. In other words, ṣalāh is not valid without wuḍū'. Purity is of different forms: purity of the external body from dirt and ḥadath (major and minor impurities), purity of the limbs from sin, purity of the heart from evil qualities, and purity of the internal self from everything besides Allāh (ﷻ). These forms of purity constitute half of īmān. The remaining half is to further beautify oneself with outward purity, noble actions, good character and focussing towards Allāh (ﷻ).`
