                commentary: `This ḥadīth explains the great reward of entrance into Paradise for one who punctually performs two rak'āts after wuḍū'. While the word طُهُوراً has been translated as wuḍū' it can equally apply to ghusl and tayammum, since purity is attained by all these methods.`
