                englishText: "We were on a journey with the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) while he was fasting. When the sun set, he said to someone: 'O so-and-so person, dismount and prepare some sawīq for us.' He said: 'O Messenger of Allāh, would you not like to wait for the night?' He said: 'Dismount and prepare some sawīq for us.' He said: 'It is still daytime.' He said: 'Dismount and prepare some sawīq for us.' So he dismounted and prepared the sawīq. The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) drank it and said: 'When you see the night advancing from this side, then the fasting person has broken his fast,' and he pointed with his hand towards the east.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Abū Dāwūd)",
