                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `The word "Mabrūr" is derived from the word birr which means obedience. Therefore, a Ḥaj Mabrūr refers to that Ḥaj in which a person does not commit any act of disobedience, even if it be minor. Some scholars have stated that it is a Ḥaj in which there is no show and ostentation. Another view is that it refers to an accepted Ḥaj. This ḥadīth shows the noble status of Ḥaj in Islām as well as the great reward it entails. This is on condition that a person performs Ḥaj with sincerity and abstains from all forms of sin.`
