                arabicText: "وعن أَبي مسعود رضي الله عنه ، قَالَ : جَاءَ رَجُلٌ إِلَى النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم بِنَاقَةٍ مَخْطُومَةٍ فَقَالَ : هذِهِ فِي سَبِيلِ اللهِ ، فَقَالَ رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : (( لَكَ بِهَا يَوْمَ الْقِيَامَةِ سَبْعُمئَةِ نَاقَةٍ كُلُّهَا مَخْطُومَةٌ )) رواه مسلم .",
                englishText: "A man came to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) with a bridled camel and said: \"This is for the path of Allāh.\" The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"For you on the day of Qiyāmah will be seven hundred camels, all of them bridled.\" (Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Muslim",
                commentary: `This ḥadīth encourages giving in the path of Allāh and shows the tremendous reward which awaits such a person in the Hereafter. It also indicates that the reward will be in accordance with the action, hence the reward of gifting a bridled camel will be seven hundred bridled camels.`
