                englishText: "Abū Ḥammād ('Uqbah ibn 'Āmir) (رضي الله عنه) narrates: I heard the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) saying while he was on the pulpit: \"'Prepare against them whatever force you can.' Power is in shooting. Power is in shooting. Power is in shooting.\" (Muslim)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Muslim",
                commentary: `In the ḥadīth, the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) quoted a verse of the Qur'ān and then explained its meaning. He repeated his explanation thrice to emphasise its importance. The ḥadīth encourages Muslims to gain proficiency in shooting. In every era, the instruments used for shooting are different. In the era of the Messenger (ﷺ), bows and arrows were utilised. In today's modern era, bullets, bombs, missiles, etc. are utilised, hence Muslims need to acquire these weapons and become proficient in using them.`
