                englishText: "A Bedouin came to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) and said: \"O Messenger of Allāh, a person fights to gain booty, another fights for fame, and another fights so that his rank may be known.\" Another narration has: \"He fights for bravery, and another fights to protect his family honour.\" Another narration has: \"He fights in anger. Which of them is in the path of Allāh?\" The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) replied: \"One who fights so that the word of Allāh may reign supreme is the one who is in the path of Allāh.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Abū Dāwūd)",
