                commentary: `A ḥadīth with similar wording was mentioned previously. See ḥadīth 8. It highlights that the promised reward for jihād is restricted to those whose intentions are correct. The objective of engaging in jihād should be to establish justice, remove oppression and establish the message of Allāh in the world. Any worldly motives, such as those mentioned in the ḥadīth, will deprive a person of the promised reward from Allāh.`
