                narrator: "Mu'āwiyah (رضي الله عنه)",
                arabicText: "وعن معاوية رضي الله عنه قَالَ : قَالَ رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : (( مَنْ يُرِدِ اللهُ بِهِ خَيْراً يُفَقِّهْهُ فِي الدِّينِ )) . متفقٌ عَلَيْهِ .",
                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"When Allāh desires good for a person, He bestows him with profound understanding of the religion.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Aḥmad, Ibn Mājah)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `This ḥadīth highlights the virtue of knowledge. It encourages us to gain profound understanding of knowledge because such understanding will guide a person to obey Allāh. The ḥadīth also indicates that beneficial knowledge is a sign of the good fortune of a person and that Allāh has desired goodness for him. Sufyān Thawrī stated, \"I do not know of anything more virtuous than acquiring knowledge.\" The \"profound understanding of the religion\" is referred to as faqāhah and one who is blessed with this is called a faqīh. Ḥasan Baṣrī stated: \"A faqīh is one who turns away from the world, is desirous of the Hereafter, has profound understanding of his religion, is continuously engaged in the worship of his Sustainer, is abstinent, does not cause any harm in respect of the Muslims, abstains from their wealth and is a well-wisher for them all.\" Those who are blessed with the understanding of religion are fortunate indeed.`
