                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Allāh is pleased with a servant who eats a morsel of food and praises Him for it, and who takes a sip of a drink and praises Him for it.\" (Muslim, Aḥmad, Tirmidhī)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Muslim",
                commentary: `It is impossible to repay Allāh for the innumerable bounties which He bestows upon us every second of the day. As an example, millions of Allāh's creations are utilised for producing every morsel of food that we eat and for the water that we drink. Even after it is consumed, Allāh has made a system of digestion and excretion. If any one of these systems has to malfunction, man will die. Therefore, it is only appropriate that we show appreciation to Allāh and acknowledge His favours. For this, we should recite the appropriate du'ās before and after meals as they include the praises of Allāh.`
