                englishText: "Abū Bakr (رضي الله عنه) said: \"O Messenger of Allāh, teach me some words which I could say in the morning and evening.\" He replied: \"Say: 'O Allāh, Creator of the heavens and the earth, Knower of the unseen and the visible, Sustainer and Master of everything. I testify that there is none worthy of worship besides You. I seek refuge in You from the evil of my self, from the evil of Shaiṭān and his prompting me to polytheism.'\" He (ﷺ) said: \"Say these words in the morning, in the evening, and when you go to sleep.\" (Tirmidhī, Aḥmad, Abū Dāwūd)",
