                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said to him and Fāṭimah (رضي الله عنها): \"When you retire to your bed – or when you lie down on your bed – say Allāhu akbar thirty-three times, Subḥānallāh thirty-three times, and al-Ḥamdulillāh thirty-three times.\" Another narration has: \"Say Allāhu akbar thirty four times.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Abū Dāwūd)",
