                englishText: "The most frequent supplication of the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) was, 'O Allāh, grant us goodness in this world, goodness in the Hereafter, and save us from the punishment of the Hell-fire.'\" The narration of Muslim adds: \"When Anas (رضي الله عنه) intended making a supplication, he would do so with any words, but he would always include these words.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Aḥmad)",
