                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) sent out a military regiment of ten people and appointed 'Āṣim ibn Thābit al-Anṣārī (رضي الله عنه) as their leader. They proceeded until they reached al-Had'ah which is between 'Usfān and Makkah. This was reported to a branch of the Hudhayl tribe called the Banū Liḥyān. About a hundred men who were all archers set out after them and began to track them. When 'Āṣim and his companions perceived their approach, they took cover at a particular spot. The archers surrounded them and said: 'Surrender and hand over yourselves. You have our promise and reassurance that we will not kill anyone of you.' 'Āṣim ibn Thābit (رضي الله عنه) said: 'O people! I have no faith in the guarantee of a disbeliever. O Allāh! Inform Your Messenger about us.' So they shot arrows at them and killed 'Āṣim.\" (Bukhārī) [The ḥadīth continues to describe how Khubayb (رضي الله عنه) was captured, sold to the Quraysh, and martyred. Before his execution, he performed two rak'āts of ṣalāh, establishing the Sunnah of praying before martyrdom. Allāh sent a swarm of bees like a cloud to protect 'Āṣim's body from the disbelievers who wanted to mutilate it.]",
