                englishText: "A person who had consumed alcohol was brought to the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ). He said: \"Beat him!\" Abū Hurayrah (رضي الله عنه) said: \"Some of us beat him with our hands, some beat him with their shoes, and some beat him with their clothes. As he was departing, someone said: 'May Allāh disgrace you!' The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: 'Do not say that. Do not help Shaiṭān against him.'\" (Bukhārī, Aḥmad, Abū Dāwūd)",
