                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"Refrain from the seven destructive sins.\" The Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم) asked: \"What are they, O Messenger of Allāh?\" He replied: \"Ascribing partners with Allāh, black magic, killing a person whom Allāh has forbidden unless for justice, consuming usury (interest), consuming the wealth of an orphan, fleeing from the battlefield, and slandering chaste, innocent believing women.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Abū Dāwūd)",
