                englishText: "Masrūq narrates: \"We visited 'Abdullāh ibn Mas'ūd (رضي الله عنه) and he said: 'O people! One who knows something should say it. One who does not know, should say: 'Allāh knows best.' It is part of knowledge to say: 'Allāh knows best', about what you do not know. Allāh said to His Messenger (ﷺ): 'Say, I do not ask you people any payment for this, and I am not among those who pretend.'\" (Bukhārī)",
