                englishText: "Sa'd ibn 'Ubādah (رضي الله عنه) fell ill, so the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) went to visit him together with 'Abd al-Raḥmān ibn 'Auf (رضي الله عنه), Sa'd ibn Abī Waqqāṣ (رضي الله عنه) and 'Abdullāh ibn Mas'ūd (رضي الله عنه). When he arrived, he found him unconscious and asked: 'Has he passed away?' They replied: 'No, O Messenger of Allāh!' The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) began to weep. When the people saw the Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) weeping, they also wept. He said: 'Are you listening! Allāh does not punish on account of tears of the eyes or the grief of the heart, but He punishes or shows mercy on account of this,' and he pointed to his tongue.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim)",
