                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `According to some scholars, buying and selling of every type of dog is prohibited, however Imām Abū Ḥanīfah and other scholars say that the prohibition is restricted to untrained dogs. Hence, if a dog is trained for hunting, then one can sell it due to the effort he has put into training it. The income of a prostitute and that of a fortune teller is Ḥarām (forbidden) according to all the scholars because of the sinful nature of their actions. Just as earning money from these sinful occupations is Ḥarām, giving money to acquire such services is also Ḥarām.`
