                narrator: "Anas (رضي الله عنه)",
                arabicText: "وعن أنسٍ ﷺ قَالَ : قَالَ رسولُ اللهِ ﷺ : (( لاَ عَدْوَى وَلاَ طِيَرَةَ ، وَيُعْجِبُنِي الفَألُ )) قالُوا : وَمَا الفَألُ ؟ قَالَ : (( كَلِمَةٌ طَيِّبَةٌ )) . متفق عَلَيْهِ .",
                englishText: "The Messenger of Allāh (ﷺ) said: \"There is no such thing as a contagious disease and there is no such thing as an evil omen, although a good omen pleases me.\" The Ṣaḥābah (رضي الله عنهم) asked: \"What is a good omen?\" He replied: \"A good word.\" (Bukhārī, Muslim, Aḥmad)",
                grade: "Sahih",
                collection: "Al-Bukhari & Muslim",
                commentary: `Some scholars state that there is no such thing as contagious diseases because all sicknesses are directly from Allāh. However, many other scholars state the Messenger's statement that "there is no such thing as a contagious disease" was in refutation of the wrong belief of the polytheists. They believed that sicknesses were contagious by their very nature and the decision of Allāh played no part in it. They rejected Allāh as the Creator of means and believed exclusively in the power of means. The Messenger sought to correct this belief and explained that these sicknesses do not spread except by the will of Allāh. For this reason, the Messenger of Allāh also said, "When you hear of a plague in a particular place, do not enter it," and "Run away from a leper as you run away from a lion," and "A sick person should not be brought before a healthy person."`
